| [Clinical laboratory](/Clinical_laboratory) sciences      |         | Diagnostic | • [Transfusion medicine](/Transfusion_medicine) is concerned with the transfusion of [blood](/Blood) and [blood component](/Blood_component), including the maintenance of a "[blood bank](/Blood_bank)".<br>• [Cellular pathology](/Cellular_pathology) is concerned with diagnosis using samples from patients taken as tissues and cells using [histology](/Histology) and [cytology](/Cytopathology).<br>• [Clinical chemistry](/Clinical_chemistry) is concerned with diagnosis by making biochemical analysis of blood, body fluids, and tissues.<br>• [Hematology](/Hematology) is concerned with diagnosis by looking at changes in the cellular composition of the [blood](/Blood) and [bone marrow](/Bone_marrow) as well as the [coagulation system](/Coagulation_system) in the blood.<br>• [Clinical microbiology](/Clinical_microbiology) is concerned with the [in vitro](/In_vitro) diagnosis of diseases caused by [bacteria](/Bacterium), [viruses](/Virus), [fungi](/Fungus), and [parasites](/Parasite).<br>• [Clinical immunology](/Clinical_immunology) is concerned with disorders of the [immune system](/Immune_system) and related body defenses. It also deals with diagnosis of [allergy](/Allergy). | Application of diagnostic techniques in [medical laboratories](/Medical_laboratories) such as [assays](/Assay), [microscope](/Microscope) analysis. |                                         |
